               <note>
                  <ab type="history">ʾAzazo is a town located 13 km ca.
                     southwest of the historic city of <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>. During the <date>17th century</date>, it became a major
                     religious and political centre and it remained a royal residence and a
                     residence of the <roleName type="function">ʾǝč̣č̣age</roleName> for much of the
                        <date>18th and 19th century</date>. Under <roleName type="title">ʾaṣe</roleName>
                     <persName ref="PRS9038Susenyos">Susǝnyos</persName> it became an important
                     residence for both the <roleName type="function">Emperor</roleName> and the
                     Jesuits. It remained the seat of the <roleName type="function">ʾǝč̣č̣age</roleName> until the <date>19th century</date>, even after the
                     establishment of the quarter of <placeName ref="LOC6535EccBet">ʾƎč̣č̣age
                        Bet</placeName> in <placeName ref="LOC3577Gondar">Gondar</placeName>. ʾAzazo
                     was the place where the monastery of <placeName ref="LOC2297DabraL">Dabra
                        Libānos</placeName> was relocated from the <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa">Šawā</placeName> (cfr. <placeName ref="LOC1670AzazoT">ʾAzazo Takla
                        Hāymānot</placeName>). </ab>
               </note>
